1 An Act to amend provisions pertaining to the public availability of information
2 contained in certain records.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 12-4-2 be AMENDED:
5 12-4-2. The county auditor has complete charge of maintaining and safeguarding
6 the voter registration records in the county. The county auditor shall retain all voter
7 registration records in the auditor's office in paper or electronic form. All such records
8 shall be open to public inspection at all times during office hours, except pursuant to
9 Except as provided in §§ 12-4-9, 12-4-9.2, and 12-4-9.3, the records must be open to
10 public inspection at all times during office hours.
11 Voter registration shall must be conducted by each county auditor and municipal
12 finance officer. Voter registration shall forms must be available at the secretary of state's
13 office and at those locations which provide driver licenses; food stamps; temporary
14 assistance for needy families; women, infants, and children nutrition program; medicaid;
15 military recruitment; and assistance to the disabled as provided by the Department of
16 Human Services any location that:
17 (1) Issues driver licenses;
18 (2) Engages in military recruitment;
19 (3) Assists disabled individuals under programs of the Department of Human Services;
20 or
21 (4) Allows for an individual to apply for:
22 (a) Supplemental nutrition assistance program benefits;
23 (b) Temporary assistance for needy families;
24 (c) Benefits under the women, infants, and children supplemental nutrition
25 program; or
26 (d) Medicaid benefits.
