1 Section 2. That § 12-4-9 be AMENDED:
2 12-4-9. The county auditor shall maintain and safeguard a digital master
3 registration file that contains:
4 (1) The information from the voter registration card of each individual registered to
5 vote in the county;
6 (2) The date of the last election at which the individual has voted;
7 (3) The date when the individual's voter information was last updated; and
8 (4) Any application made by an individual to vote by absentee ballot, including:
9 (a) The mailing address listed on the absentee ballot application form;
10 (b) The absentee ballot requested on the application;
11 (c) The date the absentee ballot was requested;
12 (d) The date that the absentee ballot was returned; and
13 (e) The method of absentee voting employed by the individual.
14 The Except as otherwise provided in this section, § 12-4-9.2, or 12-4-9.3, the
15 master registration file must be open to public inspection, free of charge. An individual's
16 social security number, driver license number, South Dakota nondriver identification
17 number, or month and day of birth is not open to public inspection.
18 The county auditor shall produce a record of all the information contained in the
19 master registration file the day before any primary or general election scheduled within
20 the county by 11:59 p.m. The county auditor shall maintain a rolling five-year archive of
21 historical information from the master registration file.
22 The county auditor shall keep a voter registration form for a purged or unregistered
23 voter twenty-two months. No purged or unregistered voter may be included in the master
24 registration file.
25 Section 3. That § 12-4-9.3 be AMENDED:
26 12-4-9.3. Home address information on the voter registration record for a
27 magistrate judge, circuit court judge, or justice of the Supreme Court eligible to vote under
28 § 12-4-1 is not open to public inspection. The Unified Judicial System shall provide a list
29 of judicial officers to the secretary of state Any personally identifiable information
30 contained in the statewide or county master registration file is not available to the public
31 if the information pertains to:
32 (1) An individual elected or appointed to statewide or legislative office;
33 (2) An individual elected or appointed to a federal office;
