1 (3) A current or retired state or federal court judge or justice; and
2 (4)(2) A law enforcement officer, as defined in § 22-1-2.
3 The Unified Judicial System shall coordinate with the United States Eighth Circuit
4 Court of Appeals and the United States District Court for the District of South Dakota to
5 provide the secretary of state with a list of individuals whose personally identifiable
6 information is not open to public inspection, pursuant to subdivision (3) (1). The director
7 of the Division of Criminal Investigation shall provide the secretary of state with a list of
8 the law enforcement officers for purposes of subdivision (4) (2).
9 For purposes of this section, "personally identifiable information" means any home
10 address, home or personal telephone number, or personal e-mail address. The city and
11 county where the official is a resident is a public record.
12 A violation of this section does not create a private right of action.
13 Section 4. That § 12-4-37.1 be AMENDED:
14 12-4-37.1. The secretary of state shall establish and maintain a rolling five-year
15 historical archive of the complete statewide voter registration file, including the weekly
16 updates published by the secretary pursuant to this section.
17 The information contained in the historical archive of the statewide voter
18 registration file must be made available free of charge.
19 An individual's social security number, driver license number, South Dakota
20 nondriver identification number, and month and day of birth contained in the historical
21 archive of the statewide voter registration file are not open to public inspection. Any home
22 address, home or personal telephone number, or the personal e-mail address contained
23 in the historical archive of the statewide voter registration file is not open to public
24 inspection if the information is for:
25 (1) An individual elected or appointed to statewide or legislative office;
26 (2) An individual elected or appointed to a federal office;
27 (3) A current or retired state or federal court judge or justice; and
28 (4)(2) A law enforcement officer, as defined in § 22-1-2.
29 The city and county where the official is a resident is a public record.
